On 9 and 10 May 2015, five people were reported to have been shot dead in the [[Switzerland|Swiss]] town of [[Würenlingen]]. One of dead may be the attacker, a Swiss national.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://bazonline.ch/panorama/vermischtes/Vermutlich-fuenf-Tote-bei-Bluttat-in-Wuerenlingen/story/17170053|title=Täter von Würenlingen war polizeibekannt|work=baz.ch/|accessdate=14 September 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-32680212|title=Swiss gunman shoots dead four in 'family dispute'|work=BBC News|accessdate=14 September 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rsi.ch/news/svizzera/W%C3%BCrenlingen-8-morti-ammazzati-4623517.html|title=Cinque morti a Würenlingen|author=RSI Radiotelevisione svizzera|work=rsi|accessdate=14 September 2015}}</ref> It is believed that the attack was a family dispute.
The offender killed his parents in law, his brother in law, the neighbour and then himself. He was known to the police for various offenses. His wife and his three children live apart from him in a secret welfare house.{{Citation needed|reason=Source needed for this secret welfare house. And a good reason for the present tense.|date=October 2016}} The misused gun was not registered and was not from army stocks. Even in a recent house search at the residence of the offender in the canton of Schwyz no gun had been found.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.srf.ch/news/schweiz/fuenf-tote-bei-beziehungsdelikt-in-wuerenlingen|title=Beziehungsdelikt in Würenlingen: Täter war polizeibekannt|work=Schweizer Radio und Fernsehen (SRF)|accessdate=14 September 2015}}</ref>
