{{Infobox ethnic group |group=Canadians in Lebanon |population= 45,000<ref>"[http://www.asiapacific.ca/sites/default/files/canadians_abroad_final.pdf Canadians Abroad: Canada's Global Asset]", ''Asia Pacific Foundation of Canada'', 26 July 2011.</ref> |regions= [[Beirut]] |langs= [[French language|French]]{{·}}[[English language|English]]{{·}}[[Lebanese Arabic]] |rels= [[Roman Catholicism in Lebanon|Roman Catholicism]]{{·}}[[Orthodox Christianity in Lebanon|Greek Orthodox]]{{·}}[[Christianity in Lebanon|Other Christians]]{{·}}[[Islam in Lebanon|Islam]] |related= [[Canadian diaspora]] }}
'''Canadians in Lebanon''' consists mostly of [[Lebanese Canadian|Canadians of Lebanese origin]] who returned to the country as well as expatriates from Canada. According to Canada's [[Department of Foreign Affairs and International Trade]], there are about 45,000 Canadians living in Lebanon<ref>"[http://www.asiapacific.ca/sites/default/files/canadians_abroad_final.pdf Canadians Abroad: Canada's Global Asset]", ''Asia Pacific Foundation of Canada'', 26 July 2011.</ref>
==History== In the 1980s, thousands of Lebanese fled their country during the [[Lebanese Civil War]] and settled in Canada.<ref>"[http://www.canada.com/nationalpost/story.html?id=82a759e4-0ff1-4ad5-a01d-fe09511986be Why 40,000 Canadians are in Lebanon] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304090942/http://www.canada.com/nationalpost/story.html?id=82a759e4-0ff1-4ad5-a01d-fe09511986be# |date=2016-03-04 }}", ''canada.com'', 21 July 2006.</ref> With the return of relative stability to the country in recent years, it has become increasingly common for members of Canada's Lebanese community to return to their homeland, most commonly for summer vacations, but also to take up residence. Most of these returnees have dual Canadian-Lebanese citizenship.
===2006 Lebanon War=== {{Main|Canadians of convenience}} Many Canadians left Lebanon and returned to Canada in the wake of the [[2006 Lebanon War]] as their houses and businesses have been destroyed during the conflict and they have no resources.
