{{no footnotes |date=December 2016}}

Farzana Majeed is a Baloch rights activist, general secretary of VBMP-Voice for Baloch Missing Persons, a non for-profit organisation working for the awareness of Baloch Missing persons in Balochistan. Farzana Baloch is known for her struggle for the recovery of Baloch missing persons. She started her campaign as an activist after her brother Zakir Majeed - a former leader of Baloch Students Organization - Wikipedia, was abducted in 2009.

Farzana Majeed has studied biochemistry from Baluchistan University and is enrolled in MPhill programme. She has marched from Quetta to Islamabad in quest of justice for his missing brother and missing persons of Balochistan.

