{{Infobox Observatory |name = Maynard F. Jordan Observatory |background = |image = |caption = |organization = [[University of Maine]] |location = [[Orono, Maine]] (USA) |coords = {{coord|44|53|56|N|68|40|3|W|type:landmark_region:US-ME|display=inline,title}} |altitude = |weather = |established = 1901 |closed = |website = [http://www.galaxymaine.com/OB/OB.htm www.galaxymaine.com/OB/OB.htm] |telescope1_name = |telescope1_type = |telescope2_name = |telescope2_type = |telescope3_name = |telescope3_type = |telescope4_name = |telescope4_type = }} '''Maynard F. Jordan Observatory''' is an [[astronomy|astronomical]] [[observatory]] owned and operated by [[University of Maine]]. Its first telescope was installed at the university in 1901, and was upgraded during the creation of the Emera Astronomy Center in 2014. It is located in [[Orono, Maine]], USA. It is the only public observatory in the state of Maine. Operated by the department of Physics and Astronomy, the eight-inch [[Alvan Clark & Sons|Alvan Clark]] telescope is housed under a roll-off roof, next to the more modern PlaneWave CDK20 in its own dome.
